Billionaires
Forbes’
34th
annual
ranking
of
the
world’s
billionaires.
For
the
2020
list,
Forbes
counted
2,095
billionaires,
58
fewer
than
a
year
ago.
Of
the
billionaires
who
remain,
51%
are
poorer
than
they
were
last
year.
In
raw
terms,
the
world’s
billionaires
are
worth
$8
trillion,
down
$700
billion
from
2019.
